Credit Ratings
STANLEY WORKS (New Britain, Conn.) -- Standard  Poor's
Corp. affirmed its single-A rating on senior unsecured debt
for this maker of do-it-yourself building and industrial
products. SP said it revised its outlook to "stable" from
"negative." About $270 million of rated debt is outstanding.
SP cited Stanley's "above-average business position" and its
cash generation strength, despite the impact of the
recession, for its decision.